          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Counting rates of all four detectors were used.",
                "Detection probability was taken as 100.%.",
                "Number of U-232 atoms in layer was defined by",
                "- counting alpha-particles from U-232 decay and its",
                "daughter elements in semiconductor alpha spectrometer,",
                "- comparison of number of fissions in U-232 layer and",
                "in a layer of U-natural, calibrated by its alpha",
                "activity and placed back-to-back with U232 layer, in",
                "thermal-neutron flux and at flux of 1000-keV neutrons.",
                "At En=100 keV, fis.c-s obtained were 2.0+-0.35 and",
                "2.6+-0.5 b, thus the weighted mean 2.2+-0.3 b.",
                "The data of energies, half-lives, alpha-decay",
                "intensities were used from:"
              ]
            }
